      "source": [
        "#import necessary libraries\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "from torchvision.models.detection import maskrcnn_resnet50_fpn\n",
        "from torchvision.transforms import functional as F\n",
        "import cv2\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the pre-trained model\n",
        "model = maskrcnn_resnet50_fpn(pretrained=True)\n",
        "model.eval()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load and preprocess the image\n",
        "def preprocess_image(image_path):\n",
        "    image = cv2.imread(image_path)\n",
        "    image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n",
        "    image_tensor = F.to_tensor(image_rgb).unsqueeze(0)\n",
        "    return image_tensor, image\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform segmentation\n",
        "def segment_objects(image_tensor, image):\n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        prediction = model(image_tensor)\n",
        "\n",
        "    masks = prediction[0]['masks'].cpu().numpy()\n",
        "    boxes = prediction[0]['boxes'].cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(len(masks)):\n",
        "        mask = masks[i, 0]\n",
        "        mask = (mask > 0.5).astype(np.uint8)\n",
        "        color = np.random.randint(0, 255, size=(3,))\n",
        "        image[mask == 1] = image[mask == 1] * 0.5 + color * 0.5\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.imshow(image)\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "image_tensor, image = preprocess_image('/content/image.jpg')\n",
        "segment_objects(image_tensor, image)\n"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "def extract_and_save_objects(original_image_path, masks, output_dir):\n",
        "\n",
        "    os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)  # Create output directory if it does not exist\n",
        "    original_image = cv2.imread(original_image_path)   # Load the original image\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "    if original_image is None:\n",
        "        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Image at path {original_image_path} not found.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "    if original_image.dtype != np.uint8:\n",
        "        original_image = original_image.astype(np.uint8)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "    height, width = original_image.shape[:2]\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i, mask in enumerate(masks):\n",
        "\n",
        "        binary_mask = (mask > 0.5).astype(np.uint8) * 255  # Convert to binary (0 or 255)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Resize the mask to match the original image dimensions\n",
        "        resized_mask = cv2.resize(binary_mask, (width, height), interpolation=cv2.INTER_NEAREST)\n",
        "        segmented_object = cv2.bitwise_and(original_image, original_image, mask=resized_mask)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Create a unique filename for the object\n",
        "        unique_id = i\n",
        "        output_file = os.path.join(output_dir, f'object_{unique_id}.png')\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Save the segmented object\n",
        "        cv2.imwrite(output_file, segmented_object)\n",
        "        print(f\"Saved object {unique_id} to {output_file}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "original_image_path = '/content/image.jpg'\n",
        "masks = np.random.rand(3, 1620, 1080)\n",
        "output_dir = 'segmented_objects'\n",
        "extract_and_save_objects(original_image_path, masks, output_dir)\n"
      ]

        "from PIL import Image\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "from transformers import CLIPProcessor, CLIPModel\n",
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the CLIP model and processor\n",
        "model = CLIPModel.from_pretrained(\"openai/clip-vit-base-patch32\")\n",
        "processor = CLIPProcessor.from_pretrained(\"openai/clip-vit-base-patch32\")\n",
        "\n",
        "def identify_object(image_path, descriptions):\n",
        "    image = Image.open(image_path)\n",
        "    image_inputs = processor(images=image, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n",
        "    text_inputs = processor(text=descriptions, return_tensors=\"pt\", padding=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Get image and text features\n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        image_features = model.get_image_features(**image_inputs)\n",
        "        text_features = model.get_text_features(**text_inputs)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Compute similarity scores\n",
        "    image_features = image_features / image_features.norm(dim=-1, keepdim=True)\n",
        "    text_features = text_features / text_features.norm(dim=-1, keepdim=True)\n",
        "    similarity = torch.matmul(image_features, text_features.T)\n",
        "    most_similar_idx = similarity.argmax().item()\n",
        "\n",
        "    return descriptions[most_similar_idx]\n",
        "\n",
        "def identify_objects_in_directory(images_dir, descriptions):\n",
        "    descriptions_dict = {}\n",
        "    for filename in os.listdir(images_dir):\n",
        "        if filename.endswith(\".png\"):  # Process only PNG files\n",
        "            image_path = os.path.join(images_dir, filename)\n",
        "            description = identify_object(image_path, descriptions)\n",
        "            descriptions_dict[filename] = description\n",
        "            print(f\"Image {filename} identified as: {description}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return descriptions_dict\n",
        "\n",
        "images_dir = 'segmented_objects'  # Directory containing segmented object images\n",
        "descriptions = [\n",
        "    \"a photo of a person\",\n",
        "    \"a photo of a bus\",\n",
        "    \"a photo of a car\",\n",
        "    \"a photo of a bag\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Identify objects in the images\n",
        "identifications = identify_objects_in_directory(images_dir, descriptions)\n",
        "print(identifications)\n"
      ]
    },

        "import pytesseract\n",
        "from PIL import Image\n",
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "pytesseract.pytesseract.tesseract_cmd = '/usr/bin/tesseract'\n",
        "def extract_text_from_image(image_path):\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        image = Image.open(image_path)\n",
        "        text = pytesseract.image_to_string(image)\n",
        "        return text\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"Error processing image '{image_path}': {e}\")\n",
        "        return \"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "def extract_text_from_directory(images_dir):\n",
        "    text_dict = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Verify the directory exists\n",
        "    if not os.path.exists(images_dir):\n",
        "        print(f\"Directory '{images_dir}' does not exist.\")\n",
        "        return text_dict\n",
        "\n",
        "    # List all files in the directory\n",
        "    files = os.listdir(images_dir)\n",
        "    if not files:\n",
        "        print(f\"No files found in directory '{images_dir}'.\")\n",
        "        return text_dict\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Process each file\n",
        "    for filename in files:\n",
        "        if filename.lower().endswith(\".png\"):  # Process only PNG files\n",
        "            image_path = os.path.join(images_dir, filename)\n",
        "            print(f\"Processing image: {image_path}\")  # Debug print\n",
        "            text = extract_text_from_image(image_path)\n",
        "            text_dict[filename] = text\n",
        "            print(f\"Text from {filename}: {text}\")\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            print(f\"Skipping non-PNG file: {filename}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return text_dict\n",
        "\n",
        "images_dir = 'segmented_objects'  # Directory containing segmented object images\n",
        "extracted_texts = extract_text_from_directory(images_dir)\n",
        "print(\"Extracted texts:\", extracted_texts)\n"
      ]
    },

        "import json\n",
        "\n",
        "def generate_summary(text):\n",
        "    if len(text.strip()) == 0:\n",
        "        return \"No text found.\"\n",
        "    return text.strip()\n",
        "\n",
        "def summarize_objects(text_dict):\n",
        "    summary_dict = {}\n",
        "    for filename, text in text_dict.items():\n",
        "        summary = generate_summary(text)\n",
        "        summary_dict[filename] = summary\n",
        "    return summary_dict\n",

        "import cv2\n",

        "# Function to annotate the image\n",
        "def annotate_image(original_image_path, masks, labels, output_image_path):\n",
        "    original_image = cv2.imread(original_image_path)\n",
        "    if original_image is None:\n",
        "        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Image not found at path: {original_image_path}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    original_image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(original_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n",
        "    pil_image = Image.fromarray(original_image_rgb)\n",
        "    draw = ImageDraw.Draw(pil_image)\n",
        "\n",
        "    colors = [(255, 0, 0), (0, 255, 0), (0, 0, 255)]\n",
        "    for i, mask in enumerate(masks):\n",
        "        mask_binary = (mask * 255).astype(np.uint8)\n",
        "        contours, _ = cv2.findContours(mask_binary, cv2.RETR_EXTERNAL, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)\n",
        "        for contour in contours:\n",
        "            cv2.drawContours(original_image, [contour], -1, colors[i % len(colors)], 2)\n",
        "        if labels[i]:\n",
        "            label_position = (10, 30 + i * 30)\n",
        "            draw.text(label_position, labels[i], fill=colors[i % len(colors)])\n",
        "\n",
        "    annotated_image_bgr = cv2.cvtColor(np.array(pil_image), cv2.COLOR_RGB2BGR)\n",
        "    if not cv2.imwrite(output_image_path, annotated_image_bgr):\n",
        "        raise IOError(f\"Failed to write image to path: {output_image_path}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Annotated image saved to {output_image_path}\")\n",
        "\n",

        "def create_summary_table(mapped_data, output_csv_path):\n",
        "    df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(mapped_data, orient='index')\n",
        "    df.to_csv(output_csv_path)\n",
        "    print(f\"Summary table saved to {output_csv_path}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Example data\n",

        "    # Flatten the arrays to compare pixel by pixel\n",
        "    true_labels_flat = true_labels.flatten()\n",
        "    pred_labels_flat = pred_labels.flatten()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Compute accuracy\n",
        "    accuracy = accuracy_score(true_labels_flat, pred_labels_flat)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return accuracy\n",

        "    true_labels = np.array([[1, 1, 0], [0, 1, 0], [1, 0, 1]])  # ground truth\n",

        "\n",
        "    accuracy = compute_segmentation_accuracy(true_labels, pred_labels)\n",
        "    print(f\"Segmentation Accuracy: {accuracy * 100:.2f}%\")\n"

        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",

        "def load_image(image_path):\n",
        "    return np.array(Image.open(image_path))\n",
        "\n",
        "def visualize_with_ground_truth(original_image, true_labels, title='Segmentation Visualization'):\n",
        "    # Ensure the original image and labels are in the correct shape\n",
        "    if original_image.ndim == 2:\n",
        "        # Grayscale image\n",
        "        original_image = np.expand_dims(original_image, axis=-1)\n",
        "    if true_labels.ndim == 2:\n",
        "        # If labels are grayscale, ensure they have a channel dimension\n",
        "        true_labels = np.expand_dims(true_labels, axis=-1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Create subplots\n",
        "    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))\n",
        "    axes = axes.flatten()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Original Image\n",
        "    axes[0].imshow(original_image, cmap='gray')\n",
        "    axes[0].set_title('Original Image')\n",
        "    axes[0].axis('off')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Ground Truth\n",
        "    # Display original image in grayscale\n",
        "    axes[1].imshow(original_image, cmap='gray')\n",
        "    # Overlay ground truth with transparency\n",
        "    axes[1].imshow(true_labels, cmap='jet', alpha=0.5)\n",
        "    axes[1].set_title('Ground Truth')\n",
        "    axes[1].axis('off')\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.suptitle(title)\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Example usage\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    # Paths to your images\n",
        "    original_image_path = '/content/image.jpg'\n",
        "    true_labels_path = '/content/segmented image.png'\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Load images\n",
        "    original_image = load_image(original_image_path)\n",
        "    true_labels = load_image(true_labels_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Visualize\n",
        "    visualize_with_ground_truth(original_image, true_labels)\n"
      ]

        "%%writefile app.py\n",
        "import streamlit as st\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "from torchvision.models.detection import maskrcnn_resnet50_fpn\n",
        "from torchvision.transforms import functional as F\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from PIL import Image\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the pre-trained model\n",
        "model = maskrcnn_resnet50_fpn(pretrained=True)\n",
        "model.eval()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load and preprocess the image\n",
        "def preprocess_image(image):\n",
        "    image_rgb = np.array(image.convert('RGB'))\n",
        "    image_tensor = F.to_tensor(image_rgb).unsqueeze(0)\n",
        "    return image_tensor, image\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform segmentation\n",
        "def segment_objects(image_tensor, image):\n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        prediction = model(image_tensor)\n",
        "\n",
        "    masks = prediction[0]['masks'].cpu().numpy()\n",
        "    boxes = prediction[0]['boxes'].cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    image = np.array(image)\n",
        "    for i in range(len(masks)):\n",
        "        mask = masks[i, 0]\n",
        "        mask = (mask > 0.5).astype(np.uint8)\n",
        "        color = np.random.randint(0, 255, size=(3,))\n",
        "        image[mask == 1] = image[mask == 1] * 0.5 + color * 0.5\n",
        "\n",
        "    return image\n",
        "\n",
        "def main():\n",
        "    st.title('Object Detection with Mask R-CNN')\n",
        "\n",
        "    uploaded_file = st.file_uploader(\"Choose an image...\", type=\"jpg\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    if uploaded_file is not None:\n",
        "        image = Image.open(uploaded_file)\n",
        "        image_tensor, image = preprocess_image(image)\n",
        "        segmented_image = segment_objects(image_tensor, image)\n",
        "\n",
        "        st.image(segmented_image, caption='Segmented Image', use_column_width=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    main()\n"
      ],
